commit.message: Add Python 3.10 to test matrix
Apply latest Black to code base
Update Black and add as pre-commit hook

jinja_filters: Updated import for Jinja 3.1.

Added some fallback imports just to reduce the possibility of breakage with
users running the latest version of typogrify and older versions of Flask/Jinja
for whatever reason.

Jinja 3.1.x has removed the jinja2.Markup function which was deprecated in Jinja
3.0.x.

See:
- https://jinja.palletsprojects.com/en/3.1.x/changes/#version-3-1-0
- https://github.com/pallets/jinja/pull/1544
Add dev docs for running tests & linters
Update installation docs & supported Python versions
Run code style linters in CI
Update changelog
Add Invoke tasks to facilitate testing and linting
Add basic Pre-commit configuration

Ignore tests when linting code

Some of the rules appropriate for non-test code can reduce readability
of the text string assertions in test code.
Add linting tools to development dependencies

Specify required Python version via caret notation

Specifying a minimum version instead would normally be preferred, but
that resulted in dependency resolution errors when other dependent
projects ostensibly used caret notation (^3.6) that translate into
implicit bracketed requirements (such as >=3.6, <4.0). Hard to tell
whether this is a Poetry bug -- since an error shouldn't result from not
specifying an upward bound -- but for now the easiest fix is to play
along and hope this is fixed so we can go back to just specifying a
minimum version.
Ignore poetry.lock

Also, switch from Setuptools to Poetry + pyproject.
